  "prompt": "What happens if I mix brown and red hair dyes together?",
  "response": "When you mix brown and red hair dyes together, you typically get a rich, warm color that combines elements of both shades. The exact result will depend on the specific shades of brown and red and the ratios in which they are mixed. Common outcomes might include auburn, chestnut, or mahogany tones. To achieve the desired result, you might want to experiment with small quantities first and adjust the proportions as needed. Always perform a strand test to see how the mixture will look on your hair before applying it all over.",
